🚨 STRICT RULE: UI LAYER PURITY (NON-NEGOTIABLE)
🔒 Core Principle

The UI (Screens & Widgets) MUST be 100% passive.
It can ONLY:

read Bloc state
send Bloc events
render UI
❌ ABSOLUTELY FORBIDDEN IN UI
1. 🚫 No Network / API Access — EVER
❌ di<Dio>()
❌ Dio() direct instantiation
❌ HTTP calls from widgets or screens

✔ Instead:

state.currentUserId
state.items
2. 🚫 No Dependency Injection Calls
❌ di<Something>() inside build()
❌ di<Something>() inside widget

✔ Only allowed:

BlocProvider(create: (_) => di<MyBloc>())
3. 🚫 No Business Logic
❌ isGroupAdmin(...)
❌ isGroupCreator(...)
❌ permission checks

✔ Must come from:

state.canEdit
state.isCreator
4. 🚫 No Data Transformation
❌ .where(...)
❌ .map(...)
❌ .sort(...)
❌ filtering / grouping / formatting lists

✔ Must come from:

state.sortedMembers
state.filteredUsers
5. 🚫 No Domain Logic Imports
❌ import domain logic helpers into UI

✔ UI only consumes ready-to-use state

6. 🚫 No Route Argument Parsing
❌ ModalRoute.of(context)

✔ Use:

constructor params
OR
typed navigation
7. 🚫 No Manual Object Construction
❌ Creating entities/models inside UI
✅ REQUIRED INSTEAD
✔ UI Must Only Do This:
final state = context.watch<EditGroupBloc>().state;

return SomeWidget(
  users: state.availableUsers,
  members: state.sortedMembers,
  canEdit: state.canEdit,
);
🧠 DATA FLOW (ENFORCED)
UI (0 logic)
   ↓
Bloc (derives UI state)
   ↓
UseCase (business logic)
   ↓
Repository
   ↓
Dio / API
🔥 ENFORCEMENT RULE (VERY IMPORTANT)

If a UI file contains ANY of the following:

Dio or direct HTTP usage
.sort(), .where(), .map()
permission checks
DI calls

➡️ It MUST be refactored immediately

🧪 TEST RULE (Quick Check)

Ask yourself:

“Can I fully test this UI by mocking ONLY the Bloc state?”

✅ YES → correct
❌ NO → architecture is broken
⚡ SHORT VERSION (FOR CURSOR)

UI must be a pure renderer:

No Dio / HTTP
No DI
No logic
No data transformation
Only Bloc state + events
